body:
hi ! I'm trying to get the `row` and the `column` from a cell, so to access these property I saw that you must access them with `cell.fullAddress`. But when i'm doing 
`console.log(cell.fullAddress);` it returns me `{ sheetName: 'Sheet1', address: 'A1', row: 1, col: 1 }`.
Or `fullAddress` is define as following:
```
fullAddress: {
  sheetName: string;
  address: Address;
  row: Row;
  col: Column;
};
```
So could you please update the doc with `rowKey: number, colKey: number` or fixing the creation cell ?
Also my worksheet is perfectly defined the file generated works perfectly

comments.body:
@CalibanAngel `Cell` has getters for `col` and `row` numbers:
https://github.com/exceljs/exceljs/blob/master/lib/doc/cell.js#L116
https://github.com/exceljs/exceljs/blob/master/lib/doc/cell.js#L119

in fact `fullAddress` should be defined as:
```
fullAddress: {
  sheetName: string;
  address: Address;
  row: number ;
  col: number ;
};
```
